Spache Word List Provenance
============================

Source: Spache, George D. "A New Readability Formula for Primary-Grade
Reading Materials." The Elementary School Journal, 1953.

Revised: Spache, George D. "Good Reading for Poor Readers." Garrard
Publishing Co., 1974.

The Spache revised word list consists of approximately 1000 words that
are familiar to children in grades 1-3. It has been widely reproduced
in educational research literature and open-source readability tools.

This word list is compiled from multiple publicly available sources in
the educational research domain. It is used here for computational
readability analysis purposes.
